%N A378380 Semiperimeter of the unique primitive Pythagorean triple whose inradius is A002315(n) and such that its long leg and its hypotenuse are consecutive natural numbers.
%D A378380 Miguel Ángel Pérez García-Ortega, José Manuel Sánchez Muñoz and José Miguel Blanco Casado, El Libro de las Ternas Pitagóricas, Preprint 2024.
%H A378380 Andrew Howroyd, <a href="/A378380/b378380.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..200</a>
%H A378380 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (40,-206,40,-1).
%F A378380 a(n) = (A377725(n) + 2*A385977(n) + 1)/2.
%F A378380 a(n) = (A002315(n) + 1)*(2*A002315(n) + 1).
%F A378380 G.f.: 6*(1 - 20*x - 13*x^2)/((1 - 34*x + x^2)*(1 - 6*x + x^2)). - _Andrew Howroyd_, Nov 16 2025
%e A378380 For n=1, the short leg is A377725(1) = 15, the long leg is A385977(1) = 112 and the hypotenuse is A385977(1) + 1 = 113 so the semiperimeter is then a(1) = (15 + 112 + 113)/2 = 120.
%t A378380 s[n_]:=s[n]=Module[{r},r=((1+Sqrt[2])^(2n+1)-(Sqrt[2]-1)^(2n+1))/2;{(r+1)(2r+1)}];semis={};Do[semis=Join[semis,FullSimplify[s[n]]],{n,0,17}];semis
%o A378380 (PARI) a(n)=my(t=polcoef((1 + x)/(1 - 6*x + x^2) + O(x*x^n), n)); (t + 1)*(2*t + 1); \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Nov 16 2025
